[4] Comment on ZMapp
From: Caroline Maxwell, independent contractor (<caroline.maxi@gmail.com>) [edited]

Re: Ebola update (68): Congo DR (NK) WHO, Uganda cases, concerns, challenges 20180815.5966397 from a report by CIDRAP: http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2018/08/drc-ebola-cases-surpass-earlier-outbreak-total-virus-infects-4-more-health

"It is not correct that ZMapp has to be stored at -20 deg C -- it is essential that it is TRANSPORTED at this temperature because it does not withstand agitation in the liquid form. Once it has arrived where it will be used, it can be stored at +4 deg C."

ProMED thanks Caroline for the correction. As she further wrote, "the incorrect information circulating may impede the use of the drug to treat patients, and although it is still an experimental treatment it appeared to show some efficacy in West Africa, and the death toll in DRC in the present epidemic is high."

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of North Kivu, Congo DR: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5971731,29837]
